 Example, a hero bracer, 9ac and 10 str 5sv disease and 5 sv poison.  So 9+10+1(round up the sv's to 15 from 10) is 20.  A Bracer of Scavenging, decent enough item, 9ac 5dex and 5stam,   9(ac)+1(for 5dex)+1(for 5 stam) adds up to only 11.    Same ac but as everyone knows the hero bracer is much better.  Something a lil closer in price, how bout a crested and a crafted helm then.  Crested helm 10ac 3cha and 6 str, a value of 16.  Crafted helm ac14 5cha 5wis and 2sv magic, value of 14.   So according to this that crown of the froglok king isnt what its cracked up to be, well, atleast for a warrior.<br><br>  I know there will be those that disagree.  But since i started goingby these rules i have seen my max damage(none critical) with my wurm go from 83 to 115(same skill and lvl yes).  I dont seem to get hit as much therefor taking less mana from the healers so its keeps the pulls comin.  When i do get hit its for less.  Haste is in the eye of the beholder i guesse, no real info on how to work it into the problem,  i will say this on it,  it eats your stamina and usually the items are low on ac.  On an added note, a warrior needs to get over 200 in strength, whether its with stats or clickable items.  Im a humi, and i made a blunder making him.  I havent made 200 in str yet but i cant wait to see what its like when i do.  As for now, every item i have,except my off hand weapon, has ac and str.   Some may want to give other stats like dexterity or agility more value.  Dexterity is good, wont add to your ac, and really not much to your damage.   Agility, takes to much to make a difference, opt for ac instead, will be cheaper.  Stamina, forget how many more hitpoints i get for points of stamina, not worth it, just get a buff is what i do.   Maybe this will help someone out there, maybe not, but here it is.  Good luck and safe journies all.<br><br><br>Klinget<br>   meatshield of 46 seasonings <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=to